HEADWORD: Enthetic
<hw>En*thet"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧n*th⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'enqetiko`s</grk> fit for inserting; <grk>'en</grk> in +
<grk>tiqe`nai</grk> to place.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Caused by a
pathogenic organism implanted in the system; <as>as, an
<ex>enthetic</ex> disease like syphilis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

